The paper proposes a framework for clustering and embedding data points, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of sampling techniques and the softmax clustering algorithm suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The mention of hierarchical clustering and the iPHD algorithm suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of modularity and the discussion of metric vs semi-metric spaces suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and social networks (cs.SI).
